{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NTQ2NjMzOTcy", "number": 2824, "title": "Adding ApolloAndroidLogger to apollo-android-support. ", "bodyText": "This introduces a helpful wrapper for the apollo-android-support module that implements the Logger interface from Apollo to output to the logcat.\nI've also added this logger to the KotlinSampleApp to log hits and misses to the HttpCache.\nHere is a sample screenshot from the logcat:", "createdAt": "2020-12-29T21:01:06Z", "url": "https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-android/pull/2824", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "9fac3b572bb3b30736846aed3565e7997dac5a4c"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2021-01-04T09:33:30Z", "author": {"login": "AdamMc331"}, "timelineItems": {"totalCount": 8, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABdq-pGwAH2gAyNTQ2NjMzOTcyOjM1ZjNlNDVjNjQ1ODJiYmViNGUzNjhhOGNhMjQzZDZkMGVhN2IwODg=", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABdslKpOgH2gAyNTQ2NjMzOTcyOjEyZjdhZTVhYjVlNjA4MmQ3YzU2NmU2ZTM4NDhjNThhNDZjNTlkNGY=", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "35f3e45c64582bbeb4e368a8ca243d6d0ea7b088", "author": {"user": {"login": "AdamMc331", "name": "Adam McNeilly"}}, "url": "https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-android/commit/35f3e45c64582bbeb4e368a8ca243d6d0ea7b088", "committedDate": "2020-12-29T18:01:04Z", "message": "Adding ApolloAndroidLogger."}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "f56c3636d199ec99a267745a40c743e1dbb3ca26", "author": {"user": {"login": "AdamMc331", "name": "Adam McNeilly"}}, "url": "https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-android/commit/f56c3636d199ec99a267745a40c743e1dbb3ca26", "committedDate": "2020-12-29T20:52:43Z", "message": "Adding logger to KotlinSampleApp Http Cache."}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "8b480321b5ab92db80f18b0864dbf81b7ed717a2", "author": {"user": {"login": "AdamMc331", "name": "Adam McNeilly"}}, "url": "https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-android/commit/8b480321b5ab92db80f18b0864dbf81b7ed717a2", "committedDate": "2020-12-29T21:00:49Z", "message": "Adding note in README.md about apollo-android-support."}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestReview", "id": "MDE3OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3NTU5Njk4ODI3", "url": "https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-android/pull/2824#pullrequestreview-559698827", "createdAt": "2020-12-29T21:02:37Z", "commit": {"oid": "8b480321b5ab92db80f18b0864dbf81b7ed717a2"}, "state": "COMMENTED", "comments": {"totalCount": 1, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0xMi0yOVQyMTowMjozN1rOIMX60A==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0xMi0yOVQyMTowMjozN1rOIMX60A==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU0OTg0NTcxMg==", "bodyText": "It's worth thinking about what this should mean for Android devs who don't want these logs in production, and whether Apollo wants to be opinionated about this. Perhaps we can provide a solution to turn them off, or just rely on devs to make sure they don't include this logger in production.\nIf we want to do that, maybe we can add some additional notes inside the documentation here.\nLet me know what y'all think!", "url": "https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-android/pull/2824#discussion_r549845712", "createdAt": "2020-12-29T21:02:37Z", "author": {"login": "AdamMc331"}, "path": "apollo-android-support/src/main/java/com/apollographql/apollo/ApolloAndroidLogger.kt", "diffHunk": "@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+package com.apollographql.apollo\n+\n+import android.util.Log\n+import com.apollographql.apollo.Logger\n+\n+/**\n+ * This is an Android wrapper around [Logger] that will take any messages Apollo wants\n+ * to print and log them in the Android logcat.\n+ */\n+class ApolloAndroidLogger : Logger {", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "8b480321b5ab92db80f18b0864dbf81b7ed717a2"}, "originalPosition": 10}]}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestReview", "id": "MDE3OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3NTU5NzQwNTIw", "url": "https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-android/pull/2824#pullrequestreview-559740520", "createdAt": "2020-12-29T23:44:50Z", "commit": {"oid": "8b480321b5ab92db80f18b0864dbf81b7ed717a2"}, "state": "COMMENTED", "comments": {"totalCount": 1, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0xMi0yOVQyMzo0NDo1MFrOIMakMA==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0xMi0yOVQyMzo0NDo1MFrOIMakMA==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDU0OTg4OTA3Mg==", "bodyText": "Maybe make it a bit more explicit?\n\n  \n    \n      \n        Suggested change\n        \n          \n    \n\n        \n      \n    \n    \n      \n          \n            \n              // optional: for additional Android utilities\n          \n          \n            \n              // optional: Most of apollo-android does not depend on Android in practice and runs on any JVM or on Kotlin native. apollo-android-support contains a few Android-only helper classes. For an example to send logs to logcat or run callbacks on the main thread.", "url": "https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-android/pull/2824#discussion_r549889072", "createdAt": "2020-12-29T23:44:50Z", "author": {"login": "martinbonnin"}, "path": "README.md", "diffHunk": "@@ -69,6 +69,8 @@ dependencies {\n   implementation(\"com.apollographql.apollo:apollo-coroutines-support:x.y.z\")\n   // optional: for RxJava3 support  \n   implementation(\"com.apollographql.apollo:apollo-rx3-support:x.y.z\")\n+  // optional: for additional Android utilities", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "8b480321b5ab92db80f18b0864dbf81b7ed717a2"}, "originalPosition": 4}]}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "d16336b62235cd444bdfc39eb4c272a5379e91e0", "author": {"user": {"login": "AdamMc331", "name": "Adam McNeilly"}}, "url": "https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-android/commit/d16336b62235cd44